1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,838
[reporter] <i>The formal summit</i>
<i>for a huge investment deal</i>

2
00:00:04,921 --> 00:00:06,256
- [pensive music playing]
- <i>between Japanese investors</i>

3
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,341
<i>and Filipino businessmen will happen soon.</i>

4
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:13,805
[Manuel, in English] This is going
to be the best day of my life.

5
00:00:13,888 --> 00:00:15,807
[Marcus] <i>General Carillo</i>
<i>is planning something.</i>

6
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:18,143
Espina and I think he'll execute it here.

7
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:19,394
Why would he do that here?

8
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:21,521
[Azuelo] <i>To create destabilization?</i>

9
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:23,523
<i>And what? To take power?</i>

10
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:25,358
<i>You better stop, Agent Reyes.</i>

11
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:26,693
[in English] <i>Goddammit!</i>

12
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:29,487
[man] <i>It's starting.</i>

13
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,281
[tense music playing]

14
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:34,200
- Sit down! Hurry up!
- [people screaming]

15
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:35,201
- [Benny] Hurry up!
- [screaming]

16
00:00:35,285 --> 00:00:37,787
[In Japanese] From now on,
you are our hostages.

17
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:39,122
[grunts]

18
00:00:39,622 --> 00:00:40,623
[man in Japanese]
<i>What's happening? Are you sure?</i>

19
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,292
- [man 1, in English] What's wrong?
- [man 2 grunts]

20
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:46,963
[Konno, in English]
That's my daughter and wife!

21
00:00:47,046 --> 00:00:49,174
[Azuelo] Agent Reyes was right.

22
00:00:49,257 --> 00:00:51,342
[Marcus, in English] <i>All units,</i>
<i>gather at the main exit points.</i>

23
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:53,094
- [siren wailing]
- [in English] <i>We move out in two minutes.</i>

24
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:56,222
[Marcus] <i>I think</i>
<i>they're working for Carillo.</i>

25
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:59,559
[Benny] <i>Don't come close</i>
<i>or we'll kill everyone here!</i>

26
00:00:59,642 --> 00:01:00,518
There's someone injured there.

27
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:03,772
[Marcus] <i>Let us send one person there</i>
<i>to treat them.</i>

28
00:01:03,855 --> 00:01:04,981
I'll go in.

29
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:06,858
[Benny] <i>It's almost 2 p.m.</i>

30
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:07,901
<i>They'll release Jennie then.</i>

31
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:09,611
We can release hostages then.

32
00:01:09,694 --> 00:01:10,570
[in English] You're not terrorists?

33
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:13,448
[in English] Is someone
forcing you to do this

34
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:15,450
<i>because Jennie was kidnapped?</i>

35
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:16,493
[Lydia] <i>Jennie's our daughter.</i>

36
00:01:16,576 --> 00:01:19,496
Those terrorists are just tricking us!

37
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:23,374
They probably planted a bomb here!

38
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:27,712
[Manuel, in English]
<i>At exactly 1:45 p.m., tomorrow,</i>

39
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:31,257
you will have to press that button.

40
00:01:31,841 --> 00:01:36,346
[Manuel] <i>You will decide whether or not</i>

41
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:40,016
<i>we will succeed.</i>

42
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:42,018
[tense music playing]

43
00:01:44,103 --> 00:01:47,148
[mysterious theme music playing]

44
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:00,954
- [man, in English] This way! This way!
- [people screaming]

45
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:02,205
[man, in English] This way!

46
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:04,332
[tense music playing]

47
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:08,294
[line ringing]

48
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:14,384
- [Lydia sobbing]
- [phone ringing]

49
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:17,762
Benny, Lydia, as I've said earlier…

50
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:20,598
I'm going to send someone in there.

51
00:02:22,016 --> 00:02:24,394
[Marcus] <i>He will not carry any weapons.</i>

52
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:28,690
He'll just treat
the wounded victim inside there.

53
00:02:28,773 --> 00:02:30,233
[in English] Waiting
for your confirmation.

54
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:33,153
[pensive music playing]

55
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:42,495
- Okay, we agree.
- [Lydia] Yes.

56
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:59,304
[timer beeping]

57
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:03,433
‪[music intensifies]

58
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:11,232
[Manuel, in English] <i>When will you stop</i>
<i>disappointing me?</i>

59
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:15,570
[sobs]

60
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:21,284
[Manuel, in English]
<i>You used to make me so proud.</i>

61
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:24,996
[in English] <i>I want to know</i>

62
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:29,167
<i>if you are still</i>

63
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:33,046
<i>the daughter that I raised!</i>

64
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:36,007
[in English] I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

65
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:38,509
[sniffles, in English] I'm sorry, Dad.

66
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:41,179
[gunshot blasts]

67
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:43,431
[indistinct murmuring]

68
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:49,354
[grim music playing]

69
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:55,109
[whimpering]

70
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:57,779
- [woman] Go ahead.
- [man, in English] Move to the exits.

71
00:03:57,862 --> 00:03:58,988
[crowd murmuring]

72
00:03:59,072 --> 00:03:59,989
[in English] Send the K9 units!

73
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:03,117
[in English] Move, move!

74
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:05,745
[foreboding music playing]

75
00:04:08,539 --> 00:04:11,084
[Manuel] Don't just stand there!
Search all of the areas!

76
00:04:23,012 --> 00:04:26,516
[morose music playing]

77
00:04:26,599 --> 00:04:30,186
[groaning in pain]

78
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:33,439
[Lydia, in English] There is a policeman
who will come to treat your wound.

79
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:36,859
[breathes shakily]

80
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,945
[in English] At 2 p.m.…

81
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:43,616
the kidnappers will release our daughter.

82
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:46,327
[in English] And we will surrender.

83
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:50,581
[in English] This will all be over.

84
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,627
- [sobs]
- [Lydia crying]

85
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,212
Sir, we're sorry.

86
00:04:57,046 --> 00:04:58,798
- It's okay.
- I'm sorry.

87
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:01,467
- [Lydia, in English] I'm sorry.
- [crying continues]

88
00:05:04,137 --> 00:05:05,805
[Benny] We're sorry, sir.

89
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:10,268
[timer beeping]

90
00:05:10,351 --> 00:05:11,686
[sobs]

91
00:05:11,769 --> 00:05:13,438
We're really sorry.

92
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:21,029
[suspenseful music playing]

93
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:27,910
[breathing heavily]

94
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:36,961
[gasping]

95
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:40,548
[suspenseful music playing]

96
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:42,133
[crowd murmuring]

97
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:52,852
[suspenseful music playing]

98
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:54,812
[Manuel] Lara!

99
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:57,356
Where is it?

100
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,111
[pensive music playing]

101
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:12,080
[inaudible]

102
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:22,840
[indistinct chatter over phone]

103
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:26,928
[pensive music playing]

104
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:41,025
[Lara crying]

105
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:44,487
[stirring music playing]

106
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:50,910
[sirens blaring]

107
00:07:04,715 --> 00:07:07,426
[stirring music continues]

108
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:26,362
- [rapid breaths]
- [footsteps approaching]

109
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:30,450
Madam! Madam!

110
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,118
What's going on with you?!

111
00:07:32,201 --> 00:07:36,372
[whimpering]

112
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,623
[Felix] Madam!

113
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:39,834
[shouts] Madam!

114
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:41,794
[Lara breathing shakily]

115
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:45,423
[intense music playing]

116
00:07:45,506 --> 00:07:47,508
[timer beeping]

117
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:51,220
‪[beeping]

118
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:02,106
[clicks]

119
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:07,737
- [explosion]
- [high-pitched ringing]

120
00:08:13,951 --> 00:08:15,495
- [man] Hey!
- [people screaming]

121
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:19,373
[suspenseful music playing]

122
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:22,919
[Omar] Jalil!

123
00:08:23,836 --> 00:08:25,379
[Teresa gasps] No! Marcus!

124
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:27,215
Marcus, my son! Marcus!

125
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,008
Marcus!

126
00:08:29,091 --> 00:08:30,009
[breathes deeply]

127
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:32,970
[Teresa] Let me go. I want to see my son!

128
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:37,058
- [gasps]
- [suspenseful music continues]

129
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,564
[breathing heavily]

130
00:08:47,235 --> 00:08:48,319
[Konno] Himari!

131
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:50,530
Yui!

132
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:52,615
Yui… [sobbing]

133
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:54,492
[sobbing]

134
00:08:57,453 --> 00:09:00,623
Yui!

135
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,711
[Konno wailing] Himari…

136
00:09:07,255 --> 00:09:09,632
[Manuel, in English] <i>Good job, Lara.</i>

137
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:11,676
[in English] <i>Good job.</i>

138
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:14,845
[suspenseful music playing]

139
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:16,222
[Lara whimpering]

140
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:19,350
‪[Lara sobbing]

141
00:09:21,018 --> 00:09:25,439
[Lara wailing]

142
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:29,819
[morose dramatic music playing]

143
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,826
[in English] Secure the perimeter!

144
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:41,539
[in English] Look
for possible survivors. Move!

145
00:09:41,622 --> 00:09:43,291
- [in English] Copy, sir. Copy, sir.
- [agent, in English] <i>Yes, sir!</i>

146
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,751
[suspenseful music playing]

147
00:09:48,629 --> 00:09:51,799
<i>We are witnessing a tragedy.</i>

148
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:54,927
<i>A tourist bus full of Japanese tourists</i>

149
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,470
<i>exploded on San Aurelio Street.</i>

150
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:57,471
<i>At this moment,</i>

151
00:09:57,555 --> 00:10:00,808
<i>we still don't know how many</i>
<i>were killed in the blast.</i>

152
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:06,272
[breathing heavily]

153
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:08,941
- What happened?
- What happened?

154
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,901
Did everyone on the bus die?

155
00:10:10,985 --> 00:10:12,153
[sobbing]

156
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:15,489
Have they found Major Espina?

157
00:10:15,573 --> 00:10:16,699
- [Teresa sobs]
- Was he caught in the explosion?

158
00:10:16,782 --> 00:10:19,160
[sobbing quietly]

159
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:23,539
[suspenseful music continues]

160
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:29,295
[line ringing]

161
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:32,089
Usman.

162
00:10:33,257 --> 00:10:34,967
Usman…

163
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:37,720
Oh Allah. [crying]

164
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,096
Son…

165
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:44,602
I told him to leave that job.

166
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:47,063
[crying]

167
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:55,363
[breathing heavily, sobbing]

168
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:04,038
[suspenseful music continues]

169
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:07,375
[sobbing quietly]

170
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:10,920
[line ringing]

171
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:27,478
[tense sinister music playing]

172
00:11:45,871 --> 00:11:49,375
[tense sinister music playing]

173
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:09,937
[Lara sobbing] <i>What have I done?</i>

174
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:15,317
[somber music playing]

175
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:16,735
[camera shutters clicking]

176
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:18,612
- [woman] Wait!
- [Edrick grunts]

177
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:20,281
- [pained grunt]
- [tense music playing]

178
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:21,907
[grunts in pain] Help!

179
00:12:22,741 --> 00:12:27,621
[groaning]

180
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:34,503
Bro!

181
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:38,299
[suspenseful music playing]

182
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:46,015
Marcus!

183
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:49,852
Espina!

184
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:55,649
[morose music playing]

185
00:12:58,402 --> 00:12:59,528
[Marcus] Espina!

186
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,447
Espina!

187
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:04,283
Espina!

188
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:07,161
Bro.

189
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:11,248
Bro. [panting]

190
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,878
Brother, I'm here. Breathe! Breathe!

191
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:17,505
Wake up.

192
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:20,257
[Lara sobbing]

193
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:21,926
What have I done?

194
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,886
- [Felix] What--
- [sobbing]

195
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:25,804
What's happening to you?

196
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:28,724
You need to calm down.

197
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:32,603
They can't see you like this, madam.

198
00:13:32,686 --> 00:13:34,063
[Lara wailing]

199
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:35,356
Madam!

200
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:39,568
Madam.

201
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:41,278
[Marcus] Bro, wake up.

202
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:44,406
Wake up. I'm here. Brother!

203
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:47,034
- Bro, wake up!
- [gasps]

204
00:13:47,576 --> 00:13:53,832
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

205
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,754
[young Gabriel] Marcus!

206
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:01,131
Don't be afraid. I've got you.

207
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:03,467
Okay, Marcus. [crying]

208
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:05,052
♪ <i>Opening my eyes after a blink</i> ♪

209
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:09,306
[grunts]Brother.

210
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:11,350
♪ <i>The throne a tyrant playing king</i> ♪

211
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:12,935
[Espina] Brother…

212
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:22,695
Bro, you're safe now. Okay?

213
00:14:22,778 --> 00:14:23,904
I'm here. Come on.

214
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:25,906
Come on.

215
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,617
♪ <i>Is only for a select few</i> ♪

216
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:32,538
♪ <i>And justice comes with a price</i> ♪

217
00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:34,665
[Marcus grunts]

218
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,793
♪ <i>I refuse to be used anymore</i>
<i>Enough is enough</i> ♪

219
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:41,463
[sobbing quietly]

220
00:14:41,547 --> 00:14:43,257
♪ <i>I will fight</i> ♪

221
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:46,302
["Maninindigan" continues]

222
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:50,931
♪ <i>Here's the situation now</i> ♪

223
00:14:51,015 --> 00:14:53,517
♪ <i>My enemy over there</i> ♪

224
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:58,355
♪ <i>A rotten system</i>
<i>Where straight gets twisted</i> ♪

225
00:14:58,439 --> 00:14:59,565
♪ <i>Can’t go along with it</i> ♪

226
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:04,653
[Lara crying]

227
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:05,571
Madam.

228
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,364
Madam!

229
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:13,579
[sobbing]

230
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:17,541
[tense music playing]

231
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,919
[breathes heavily]

232
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:21,211
[whimpers]

233
00:15:22,796 --> 00:15:25,257
[cries, sobs]

234
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:29,261
[Lara whimpers]

235
00:15:35,643 --> 00:15:37,686
[music fades]

236
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:41,565
[unsettling music playing]

237
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:42,691
[Teresa] Marcus!

238
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:45,069
Take him straight to Trauma Room One!

239
00:15:45,152 --> 00:15:47,112
Doc, I'll assist you!

240
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:48,781
[Jamilah] <i>Hurry!</i>

241
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:51,367
[unsettling music continues]

242
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:09,760
It looks like Usman
wasn't caught in the explosion.

243
00:16:10,594 --> 00:16:12,012
Really?

244
00:16:12,096 --> 00:16:13,097
[exhales]

245
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:18,352
Thank you, Allah.

246
00:16:18,435 --> 00:16:19,687
Thank you. [whimpers]

247
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:21,730
[clicks tongue]

248
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:24,984
But what about Benny and Lydia?

249
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,151
What could have happened to them?

250
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:28,195
And the child Jennie.

251
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:30,864
Where could she have gone?

252
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:34,576
[Jennie whimpers]

253
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:36,704
[crying]

254
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:38,372
- [man] Get down!
- [crying, whimpering]

255
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:39,748
Mama!

256
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:41,166
- Papa!
- [tires screeching]

257
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:48,173
[crying, whimpering]

258
00:16:51,218 --> 00:16:57,016
[crying, sobbing]

259
00:16:59,893 --> 00:17:01,437
[Jennie] Mama! Papa!

260
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:04,314
- [Jennie] Where are you?!
- Jennie?!

261
00:17:04,398 --> 00:17:05,441
Jennie!

262
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:08,402
[both whimpering]

263
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:09,945
Where have you been?

264
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:13,532
Two men took me.

265
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,826
Wait, how did you get here?

266
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:18,287
They just left me there all of a sudden.

267
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:20,664
Where? Show me. Can you point it out?

268
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:22,750
Come on, let's go there.

269
00:17:23,584 --> 00:17:24,626
[Suher] Where did they leave you?

270
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,462
- [Jennie] Over there.
- [Suher] Come on, show me.

271
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:28,255
- [Jennie] There.
- [Suher] Come on, let's hurry.

272
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:29,965
[Suher] Where?

273
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,051
[Jennie] Over there.

274
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:33,093
[Suher] There?

275
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:34,595
[Jennie] Yes, over there.

276
00:17:34,678 --> 00:17:36,513
[Suher] But there's no vehicle.

277
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,515
[Jennie] Because they already left.

278
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,475
[Jennie crying]

279
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,226
What? You were left there?

280
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,812
- [Jennie] Yes. [crying]
- Was it a white van? Tell me.

281
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:46,523
No, it was a dark van.

282
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:48,025
- [whimpers]
- A dark van?

283
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:50,319
[whimpering]

284
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:52,529
[unsettling music playing]

285
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:58,452
[Jennie crying]

286
00:17:58,535 --> 00:18:01,371
Hey, don't cry anymore.
It's okay, it's okay.

287
00:18:01,455 --> 00:18:04,917
[whimpering, crying]

288
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,001
Stop crying.

289
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:10,964
- [Jennie whimpering, crying]
- [unsettling music continues]

290
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:16,470
[sobbing, crying]

291
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:20,390
Omar, I'm going to the hospital.

292
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:21,934
I can't leave my son.

293
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:24,144
Wait, Datu Rahman, calm down.

294
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:26,647
We can't go to your son at the hospital

295
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:28,857
while he's still pretending to be Espina.

296
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:30,984
His mission might be compromised,

297
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:34,905
and he'll be exposed as Jalil
if we go to the hospital.

298
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:39,701
Let's just trust Allah not to abandon him.

299
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:42,329
[unsettling music playing]

300
00:18:45,082 --> 00:18:46,542
[phone buzzing]

301
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,382
Hello, Father?

302
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:56,468
Jamilah, where is your brother Jalil?

303
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:58,846
Jalil was rushed to this hospital.

304
00:18:58,929 --> 00:18:59,721
[gasps]

305
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:03,225
He's still unconscious,
but he's in stable condition.

306
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:05,435
[in Arabic] Praise be to God.

307
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:07,354
That's good.

308
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:09,857
Keep me updated.

309
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:12,151
I wanted to go there,

310
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:14,862
but it might cause more chaos.

311
00:19:15,529 --> 00:19:16,738
Don't worry, Father.

312
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,533
I'll take care of Jalil. I'll monitor him.

313
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,202
[in Tausug] Thank you, Jamilah.

314
00:19:23,453 --> 00:19:24,872
Be careful there.

315
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:26,540
Okay, Father.

316
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:32,629
[dramatic sting]

317
00:19:41,805 --> 00:19:44,808
[pensive music playing]

318
00:19:46,185 --> 00:19:47,227
Reyes.

319
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:50,147
Bro, how are you?

320
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,819
You had us worried.

321
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,280
[Teresa] Are you still in pain anywhere?

322
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:05,537
I need to leave now.

323
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:06,955
[Teresa] Oh, wait, wait, wait.

324
00:20:07,039 --> 00:20:07,873
- [Teresa] Not yet.
- [groans]

325
00:20:07,956 --> 00:20:09,875
[Teresa] Your body might go into shock.

326
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:12,753
You took a heavy hit
from the explosion earlier,

327
00:20:12,836 --> 00:20:15,672
so you still have a slight concussion.

328
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,382
You need to rest first.

329
00:20:17,466 --> 00:20:18,800
Reyes.

330
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,011
We still have a lot to do.

331
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:23,222
Bro, don't think about work for now.

332
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:26,225
I'll handle it.

333
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:28,268
Stay here and recover.

334
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:33,065
By the way…

335
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:36,860
we don't know how to contact your family.

336
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:44,785
[Teresa] Do you have their number?

337
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:47,704
- We're sure they're worried about you.
- [door clicks shut]

338
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:50,374
Excuse me.

339
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,335
[plate thuds]

340
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,007
Don't bother.

341
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,969
They're far away.

342
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:04,888
- Mm.
- They won't be able to come here either.

343
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:07,307
[pensive music continues]

344
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:09,643
In that case,

345
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:12,396
Marcus and I will take care
of you for now.

346
00:21:14,856 --> 00:21:15,941
[Jamilah] Major Espina.

347
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:18,277
Good thing you're already
in stable condition.

348
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:21,029
Thank you, Jamilah.

349
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,744
And you too, Agent Reyes.

350
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:30,122
I'm glad you're safe.

351
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:34,876
Same goes for the rest of your TFA team.

352
00:21:36,128 --> 00:21:37,379
Thank you.

353
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:44,303
[pensive music continues]

354
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:55,063
[Jamilah] <i>I couldn't even</i>
<i>properly check on you.</i>

355
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:57,107
- [pensive music playing]
- <i>I couldn't even hug you.</i>

356
00:21:57,190 --> 00:22:01,236
[sobs] Because they might
find out your real identity.

357
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,989
[Azuelo] If Carillo
is really behind all of this,

358
00:22:04,072 --> 00:22:05,657
who are his accomplices?

359
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:07,075
[Azuelo] <i>Where is Agent Angeles?</i>

360
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:09,244
She got off the tactical van
before the bus exploded.

361
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:11,913
We haven't seen her since
we returned from the mission.

362
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:13,915
[reporter] Should we blame the government?

363
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:17,878
Please, let's not blame the government.

364
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,297
[Azuelo] <i>You bastard!</i>

365
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,883
You've been playing with all of us.

366
00:22:22,966 --> 00:22:24,926
There are many bad people

367
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:26,428
who are willing to destroy everything

368
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:29,556
<i>just for their own agenda.</i>

369
00:22:30,057 --> 00:22:32,184
[in English] This is all your fault!

370
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:34,728
But we shouldn't lose hope even more.

371
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:36,813
[Marcus] <i>Because in the coming days,</i>

372
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:39,274
<i>we will face a much bigger problem.</i>

373
00:22:39,357 --> 00:22:40,734
We need to be ready.

374
00:22:40,817 --> 00:22:41,818
[Jalil] <i>I don't know</i>

375
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:43,862
<i>if I remember this</i>
<i>from when I was a child.</i>

376
00:22:43,945 --> 00:22:46,698
I have a brother, and he's saving me.
